<TABLE CLASS="SPELLS" WIDTH=100%>
<TR><TH>You're right...<BR>
<I><FONT SIZE=-1>Posted 2000-03-21 20:18:05 by Not Bogus!!!</FONT></I></TH></TR>
<TR><TD>You're right, you couldn't get anything but a blue con on your pet as a 6th. This is because the spell summons a pet which is within a level of the level you got the spell at, just like with the other pet classes.  This means that this 4th level spell gives you a pet from 3rd to 5th.  However, due to a recent patch, the green con of a pet was bumped up to blue.  This is due to the fact that there is a disparity between character levels and monster levels.  You notice that as you gain levels, white/black conning monsters get harder and harder to solo, don't you?  This lasts until somewhere in the late teens for most classes, at which point, soloing is no longer feasable.  You just can't do it anymore.  Warriors start needing buffs and heals, magi need tanks, etc.  This is because as the levels increase, monsters get more powerful quicker than PC's.  So does your pet, though.  As you get higher in level, your pets will start getting lower in levels, but still be able to trounce many things, which is the reason for the patch.  Who wants to be misled that their pet, who just happens to be of a level to con green, is completely useless?</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
